URL reference: https://www.sysdig.com/blog/leveling-up-kubernetes-posture-from-baselines-to-risk-aware-admission
DateReviewed: 2026-04-02
Description: This article talks about Kubernetes security posture - how you set up your cluster to respond to various threats. We dive right in, talking a bit about some different pieces that are built into K8s by default. They do point out that some of these tools aren't fine grained - they permit or deny, but don't always take context into account - should this pod be able to do this NOW and HERE? They then contrast usual things like admission controllers with Kyverno and OP gatekeeper - stopping something from running at all vs checking at runtime. This is an interesting discussion, and shows the need for understanding on the security front.
BottomLine: Good discussion and thought piece on Kubernetes secuity approaches
